WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:01.760
Hey, good morning, family.

00:00:01.760 --> 00:00:04.640
I'm excited to be with you all again today.

00:00:04.640 --> 00:00:06.390
I was praying and I was asking the Lord.

00:00:06.390 --> 00:00:08.446
I said, 'What do you want me to tell your people?

00:00:08.446 --> 00:00:18.445
' And he said, 'Brandon, I want you to go back and I want you to tell them again about your incident that happened with your dog, with your daughter.

00:00:18.445 --> 00:00:20.506
' And I said, 'Okay, well, I can do that.

00:00:20.506 --> 00:00:23.359
' But it's a very hard story for me to tell.

00:00:23.359 --> 00:00:26.411
It's a pride buster.

00:00:26.411 --> 00:00:27.417
It's a flesh buster.

00:00:27.417 --> 00:00:30.120
It's everything for me because of how I acted.

00:00:30.120 --> 00:00:36.160
But the Lord wants you to know that you don't have to be perfect to serve him.

00:00:36.160 --> 00:00:45.416
You don't have to be somebody that is walking around like a holy angel choir singing behind them all the time for God to use them.

00:00:49.800 --> 00:00:50.130
I want you to understand today that it's all by grace.

00:00:54.880 --> 00:00:55.280
And here's what I did.

00:00:55.280 --> 00:00:57.680
I did something really stupid.

00:01:08.676 --> 00:01:08.960
My son and I were playing a game.

00:01:13.920 --> 00:01:16.773
It was right after Christmas and we were on Christmas break, and we were playing a game online together and we were just having fun.

00:01:25.680 --> 00:01:25.930
My daughter was playing with the puppy that I got her for Christmas, and it was a small little dog.

00:01:31.671 --> 00:01:37.920
I felt inside before, when she was playing with this dog, I told her, 'Honey, you need to put the dog up.

00:01:42.915 --> 00:01:49.120
I don't know, you just need to put the dog up.

00:01:49.120 --> 00:01:58.879
Don't let the dog run around by my feet and everything,' because the dog was sitting there nipping at my toes and was just playing around, you know.

00:02:09.599 --> 00:02:09.815
And so I told my daughter, I said, 'You need to put the dog up, honey.

00:02:09.815 --> 00:02:13.316
' And so I thought she had already obeyed and put the dog up.

00:02:25.040 --> 00:02:25.634
She was sitting there coloring in her coloring book and was over here to my side, but I didn't know that she had put the dog underneath my feet in a blanket.

00:02:27.496 --> 00:02:38.319
And so I jumped up to go to the bathroom real quick because I put the game on pause with my son, and I jumped up and I landed on that dog and I crushed it completely.

00:02:38.319 --> 00:02:39.652
Guts came out the side.

00:02:39.652 --> 00:02:41.400
Blood was coming out the nose.

00:02:42.210 --> 00:02:52.103
The dog was shaking profusely, and then all of a sudden, I picked up the dog and I'm looking at it, and the dog just died in my hands because I crushed it.

00:03:05.260 --> 00:03:05.640
So I lost it.

00:03:08.448 --> 00:03:08.624
I started using bad words.

00:03:10.520 --> 00:03:14.062
I started yelling at my daughter because of what she did, putting the dog underneath my feet.

00:03:17.903 --> 00:03:18.239
And I just lost it, y'all.

00:03:18.239 --> 00:03:25.120
I'm embarrassed to say it, but I lost my temper and I shouldn't have done it, you know.

00:03:25.840 --> 00:03:28.399
And so I was screaming at my little girl for not obeying me.

00:03:33.480 --> 00:03:33.689
I was mad at the situation.

00:03:33.689 --> 00:03:35.080
Bottom line is, I acted a fool.

00:03:39.804 --> 00:03:40.027
I acted like a total you-know-what.

00:03:42.710 --> 00:03:43.959
I shouldn't have done it.

00:03:44.319 --> 00:03:46.583
And me, freaking out, I'm screaming and yelling, 'Why did this happen?

00:03:47.314 --> 00:03:48.391
You know, you should have obeyed and you didn't!

00:03:48.391 --> 00:03:50.377
' And I'm mad at my wife.

00:03:57.670 --> 00:03:57.955
I'm mad at everybody.

00:03:59.268 --> 00:04:08.520
I'm blaming everybody other than myself for not looking at the dog below because I acted a fool.

00:04:24.809 --> 00:04:25.164
And I'm so upset at the dead dog in my hand, and I was looking at it as a total loss.

00:04:27.374 --> 00:04:27.639
I mean, it's gone.

00:04:31.660 --> 00:04:31.973
And so I'm like, 'You know what?

00:04:31.973 --> 00:04:34.387
It is what it is.

00:04:34.387 --> 00:04:36.880
' So I freaked out.

00:04:37.280 --> 00:04:46.764
And so I took the dog, and my wife had a shoe box, and I said, 'Put that dog in that shoe box and put it out on the porch.

00:04:47.378 --> 00:04:50.248
I don't want to deal with it.

00:04:50.248 --> 00:05:00.240
' It was because it was cold, and here in Oklahoma, it gets really cold and the ground was frozen, and I knew that there was no way I could dig a hole in the middle of the night.

00:05:02.280 --> 00:05:05.040
It just had snowed and it was freezing cold.

00:05:05.040 --> 00:05:09.080
So I said, 'Put the dog in the shoe box and put it on the porch.

00:05:10.079 --> 00:05:11.626
I don't want to deal with it right now.

00:05:11.626 --> 00:05:20.740
' And so my little girl turned to me and she said, 'Daddy, aren't you going to pray for it to be raised from the dead?

00:05:20.740 --> 00:05:25.849
' And I said, 'Honey, God's not going to hear me when I pray right now for that dog to be raised.

00:05:31.189 --> 00:05:31.394
You pray.

00:05:31.394 --> 00:05:32.560
' I said, 'I'm not there.

00:05:33.080 --> 00:05:33.280
You pray.

00:05:33.280 --> 00:05:37.395
' She said, 'All things are possible to him who believes,' like that to me.

00:05:38.390 --> 00:05:39.439
I told her, 'I'm not there.

00:05:44.860 --> 00:05:45.120
I just acted out, and the Lord's not going to hear me when I pray.

00:05:45.508 --> 00:05:45.702
You pray.

00:05:45.702 --> 00:05:51.839
' So, she started marching up and down the hall, just saying, 'All things are possible to him that believes.

00:05:51.839 --> 00:05:56.020
' And at this time, I left the room because I was so angry.

00:06:02.119 --> 00:06:02.299
I had to get some space.

00:06:12.285 --> 00:06:12.650
So, I went into our bedroom and I shut the door and I prayed.

00:06:12.650 --> 00:06:15.839
I asked God—because I lost it so bad.

00:06:15.839 --> 00:06:22.446
And I could hear my little girl up and down the hall, 'In the name of Jesus, get up from the dead!

00:06:22.446 --> 00:06:24.789
In the name of Jesus, get up from the dead!

00:06:24.789 --> 00:06:29.716
' And needless to say, that dog was dead in that box.

00:06:29.716 --> 00:06:35.936
My wife had put it outside in the cold.

00:06:44.950 --> 00:06:45.380
It was completely cold outside and everything was frozen.

00:07:08.114 --> 00:07:08.508
And I told her to put it in the trash can or whatever, and I would deal with it in the morning.

00:07:08.508 --> 00:07:19.244
Well, I was praying, and all of a sudden, an hour goes by, two hours go by, and I come back in and I make amends with the family.

00:07:19.613 --> 00:07:21.653
And I told them, 'I'm sorry.

00:07:26.548 --> 00:07:26.902
I just acted a fool.

00:07:30.926 --> 00:07:31.360
I acted out of anger.

00:07:31.360 --> 00:07:34.560
It was all based out of fear.

00:07:35.314 --> 00:07:36.889
I was afraid of the loss, afraid of everything.

00:07:37.080 --> 00:07:42.266
I was blaming myself, I was blaming you, and the way I handled it, I'm sorry.

00:07:42.266 --> 00:07:51.320
' And I apologized, you know, and I took communion over it, and I put it at the foot of Jesus.

00:07:51.320 --> 00:07:52.919
That's where I was.

00:08:05.199 --> 00:08:05.489
My little girl was still crying, still upset.

00:08:08.970 --> 00:08:13.060
I was holding her at that time, 'Baby, I'm sorry I yelled at you and freaked out at the situation.

00:08:13.060 --> 00:08:16.909
I'm sorry you lost your dog.

00:08:16.909 --> 00:08:17.474
We'll replace him.

00:08:17.474 --> 00:08:19.993
But God's got this, you know.

00:08:19.993 --> 00:08:24.899
' And I was just trying to comfort her, comfort the family because of my actions and everything.

00:08:24.899 --> 00:08:29.389
So, my wife goes, like I said, this is about two hours later.

00:08:32.457 --> 00:08:34.342
She goes to take the trash out, and I hear her say, 'The dog's gone.

00:08:37.093 --> 00:08:37.316
It wasn't in the shoe box anymore.

00:08:37.316 --> 00:08:40.124
' So, I thought the raccoons had gotten the dog.

00:08:43.760 --> 00:08:46.692
And so, you know, I'm sitting there, and all of a sudden, she says, 'I hear a squeaking noise.

00:08:46.692 --> 00:08:50.366
' And it was like, 'Squeak, squeak.

00:08:50.366 --> 00:08:54.590
' She said, 'I hear a squeaking noise.

00:08:54.590 --> 00:09:06.399
' She starts looking down, and she sees the dog at the bottom of the trash can, alive, completely alive, begging, wagging its tail, begging to get out of that trash can.

00:09:06.399 --> 00:09:10.568
She goes and tips the trash can over, grabs that dog, and pulls it out.

00:09:10.568 --> 00:09:13.600
God had completely restored all that dog's guts back inside.

00:09:13.600 --> 00:09:17.537
The blood was completely wiped off of it.

00:09:21.279 --> 00:09:26.160
There were no signs of any kind of trauma on this dog at all.

00:09:26.160 --> 00:09:28.846
God had completely done a creative miracle on that dog.

00:09:29.634 --> 00:09:38.000
And my wife brought that little puppy in, and it was shivering cold because it was freezing, which is a miracle in itself because of how cold it was.

00:09:58.000 --> 00:09:58.200
And the dog was shaking.

00:10:05.080 --> 00:10:05.360
And so we put a blow dryer on the dog and started heating that dog up.

00:10:07.320 --> 00:10:09.759
And my little girl was screaming, 'I told you all things are possible to him that believes!

00:10:11.200 --> 00:10:11.908
I told you all things are possible to him that believes, Daddy!

00:10:19.444 --> 00:10:19.827
I told you he would bring him back!

00:10:29.020 --> 00:10:29.200
I told you he'd bring him back!

00:10:29.200 --> 00:10:31.740
' because I trained my children to believe the impossible.

00:10:36.079 --> 00:10:36.586
I trained my children to believe that Jesus is the same yesterday, today, and forever.

00:10:38.360 --> 00:10:44.640
And the same Jesus that healed the sick 2,000 years ago even cares about a dog that dies in the bottom of a trash can.

00:10:44.640 --> 00:10:46.507
He will even touch your dog.

00:10:46.507 --> 00:10:48.360
He's no respecter of persons.

00:10:49.680 --> 00:10:53.573
I believe with all my heart that the faith of a mustard seed can move a mountain.

00:10:53.573 --> 00:10:56.600
I believe even a childlike faith can bring a dog back.

00:10:56.600 --> 00:10:58.400
All things are possible to him who will believe.

00:10:59.714 --> 00:11:01.230
And that's what He did that day for her.

00:11:01.230 --> 00:11:12.124
She came down that hall and she's loving that little dog and she's holding it in her hands and she was saying, 'Daddy, I told you all things are possible to him who believes.

00:11:12.124 --> 00:11:24.939
' And she kept saying it over and over again, just rejoicing and loving that dog and lifting it up in the air and rejoicing because of what God had just done for her.

00:11:24.939 --> 00:11:42.580
When my wife brought that dog in and it was complete—no guts, no blood, no nothing out of his nose, all bones restored, walking around like normal again, all of it completely like nothing had ever happened—it was like a holy hush in my house.

00:11:48.010 --> 00:11:51.960
The presence of the Lord was so strong, and you could feel it.

00:11:51.960 --> 00:11:56.160
But this is what I want to say to you.

00:11:57.320 --> 00:12:03.700
I had it in my heart, and the Lord told me, and I'll say it again to you all.

00:12:10.192 --> 00:12:19.928
The Lord said this to me: 'Brandon, even on your best day'—because I thought in my mind, this is what I thought, 'Man, if I would have prayed for it, or whatever,' making all these excuses up in my head and talking to him about everything, and I was like, 'Wow!

00:12:19.928 --> 00:12:22.969
' And he stopped me and he corrected me immediately.

00:12:22.969 --> 00:12:32.267
He said this to me: 'Brandon, even on your best day, son, your righteousness is as filthy rags to me.

00:12:32.267 --> 00:12:36.560
Even on your best day, you cannot earn the anointing.

00:12:36.560 --> 00:12:39.067
You cannot earn your salvation.

00:12:39.067 --> 00:12:41.084
You cannot earn healing.

00:12:41.084 --> 00:12:42.996
It's all by grace.

00:12:51.090 --> 00:12:51.400
I paid the price for you for all of it.

00:12:54.368 --> 00:12:55.610
And I raised that dog up as a sign and wonder to your little girl.

00:12:55.610 --> 00:12:57.430
' Do you get that, y'all?

00:12:57.430 --> 00:13:03.493
He brought the dog back, and he did it just for a child.

00:13:08.059 --> 00:13:11.899
And that's what I'm trying to tell you.

00:13:11.899 --> 00:13:14.480
She was down there, and she prayed.

00:13:20.840 --> 00:13:21.040
Like I said, that's the way we raise our children.

00:13:21.040 --> 00:13:25.120
We believe with all our heart that Jesus Christ is still doing miracles today.

00:13:25.120 --> 00:13:36.320
And I just want to tell you all, people are always asking me about my faith walk and everything, and I just want to tell you I'm just normal.

00:13:38.440 --> 00:13:38.660
I'm just a normal human being.

00:13:38.660 --> 00:13:40.420
I've got issues just like everybody else.

00:13:47.360 --> 00:13:47.839
I'm a work in progress.

00:13:47.839 --> 00:13:53.160
I take one day at a time, and I seek his face every single day.

00:13:53.160 --> 00:14:01.879
I seek him for finances, I seek him to provide for my family as the head of my house, and for better jobs.

00:14:01.879 --> 00:14:07.812
I pray that over us: 'Father, increase our hands so we can be a blessing to your people.

00:14:07.812 --> 00:14:16.540
' You can't be a real blessing a lot of times if you're broke and making it from paycheck to paycheck, only having enough to pay your bills and borrowing the rest.

00:14:16.540 --> 00:14:18.160
So that's where I'm at.

00:14:18.160 --> 00:14:19.560
I'm always believing for the supernatural.

00:14:19.560 --> 00:14:23.319
I'm always believing for the impossible, that God is able to do it today.

00:14:23.319 --> 00:14:35.530
I even told you about the time—my son is sitting behind the camera right now—we had another dog that was born dead, completely dead, rigid.

00:14:35.530 --> 00:14:40.628
It was stiff as a board, nasty, coming out green all over.

00:14:40.628 --> 00:14:42.182
It was nasty.

00:14:45.360 --> 00:14:49.600
And the Lord told me, 'I'm going to start to deal with you with creative miracles, and I'm going to train you through animals.

00:14:49.600 --> 00:14:59.360
I'm going to let you practice this way, and I'm going to train you and teach you how to do these things.

00:14:59.360 --> 00:15:01.017
' And so, you know what?

00:15:03.371 --> 00:15:03.634
The dog was born dead.

00:15:05.707 --> 00:15:06.222
And he said, 'Take the dog, brush it off.

00:15:06.222 --> 00:15:10.079
' And it was purple, it was dead, everything, born that way.

00:15:19.901 --> 00:15:20.150
So, I took the dog in my hand, and I held it there.

00:15:20.150 --> 00:15:24.595
My son was there, and we were watching it, and he's sitting right by my side.

00:15:24.595 --> 00:15:30.560
I put the dog in my hand, and the Lord said, 'Now, I want to teach you something.

00:15:30.560 --> 00:15:39.520
Speak to the dog and tell it to come back in the name of Jesus and the authority of the name of Jesus.

00:15:39.520 --> 00:15:46.253
' And so I said, 'In the name of Jesus, I command you to get up.

00:15:46.253 --> 00:15:54.539
In Jesus' name, you will live and not die, and you will come back right now in Jesus' name.

00:15:54.539 --> 00:15:56.800
' And that dog gasped for air.

00:15:56.800 --> 00:16:12.194
All of a sudden, I felt the power of God come out of my fingers like electricity, and it went into that dead dog's body and the dog's heart—I could feel it start to beat in the palm of my hand.

00:16:13.900 --> 00:16:16.869
And I could feel the lungs start to fill up with air.

00:16:29.644 --> 00:16:29.876
And all of a sudden, what was a completely purple, lifeless dog started having pink pigment to its skin.

00:16:29.876 --> 00:16:39.139
It started coming back, and everything—the life of all the blood from the heart pumping—started getting everything back alive again right there.

00:16:40.513 --> 00:16:47.200
And my son was sitting there just like he's sitting behind the camera right now; he saw all of it.

00:16:47.200 --> 00:16:51.320
In my amazement, I was just like, 'Oh my gosh, what just happened?

00:16:51.320 --> 00:17:03.440
' You know, just to see something come back from the dead was a huge deal for me because I believe in God all the time that I'm going to raise people from the dead.

00:17:14.046 --> 00:17:14.309
And I believe with all my heart we're going to do those things.

00:17:14.309 --> 00:17:16.640
Signs and wonders will follow those that believe.

00:17:34.320 --> 00:17:34.686
And I'm telling you all, we are in the last of the last days.

00:17:35.783 --> 00:17:39.580
And a lot of people say, 'Oh, I've heard that before.

00:17:43.169 --> 00:17:43.539
Jesus isn't coming anytime soon.

00:17:43.539 --> 00:17:44.650
' Whatever.

00:17:44.650 --> 00:17:45.760
He's coming.

00:17:45.760 --> 00:17:53.689
I've seen him face to face, and he told me to tell you he's coming, and Jesus is coming.

00:17:53.689 --> 00:18:02.987
And you better get your house right before him, repent, and get your sins all washed in the blood because if you don't, you're going to turn or you're going to burn.

00:18:08.811 --> 00:18:09.039
And that's the bottom line.

00:18:09.039 --> 00:18:21.450
You're either going to get saved and get right before the Lord, or you're going to get left because the rapture of the church is about to happen, and we're going to get out of here.

00:18:21.450 --> 00:18:26.836
Whether that's 10 years, 20 years, or whatever, that's nothing compared to the 2,000 years that we've been waiting.

00:18:27.093 --> 00:18:28.124
It could be tomorrow.

00:18:28.124 --> 00:18:36.800
So, you always want to have your lamps full and be seeking him daily instead of just on Sunday.

00:18:46.693 --> 00:18:49.938
You need to have a relationship with the King because Jesus loves you and he wants the best for you, but you're not going to be able to have a part-time relationship with God for a full-time devil.

00:18:53.663 --> 00:18:55.783
You have to have a full-time relationship with God because the devil's not going to be after you just part-time.

00:18:55.783 --> 00:18:59.1000
He's going to try to kill, steal, and destroy all the time.

00:18:59.1000 --> 00:19:02.299
That's the kind of devil he is.

00:19:05.623 --> 00:19:06.720
And you may say, 'Well, the devil hasn't been messing with me.

00:19:06.720 --> 00:19:09.886
' Well, it's probably because you aren't a threat to him.

00:19:20.987 --> 00:19:21.360
You aren't trying to do something to affect his kingdom.

00:19:32.409 --> 00:19:32.698
And he's not going to sit back idly by and not mess with people who are a threat to him.

00:19:32.698 --> 00:19:46.924
So, you've got to realize you've got to put your armor on today, put your big boy pants on, and go out there and do what God's commissioned you to do: pray for the sick, raise the dead, cast out devils.

00:19:46.924 --> 00:19:51.315
Freely you've been given, freely you give it out.

00:20:05.634 --> 00:20:05.966
That's the kind of Jesus we serve.

00:20:15.072 --> 00:20:15.304
He came to save that which was lost.

00:20:15.304 --> 00:20:21.740
And I'm telling you, the greatest harvest of souls that this world has ever seen is yet to happen.

00:20:27.949 --> 00:20:28.286
The greatest outpouring of Joel chapter 2, we're about to see the former and the latter rain together.

00:20:28.286 --> 00:20:40.270
We're about to see great signs and wonders throughout the whole world—seeing arms and legs and eyes and ears popping open, the dead being raised, casting out devils.

00:20:40.270 --> 00:20:47.320
We're going to see some of the greatest miracles this world has ever seen or ever heard of.

00:20:47.320 --> 00:20:50.896
And I'm telling you, it's time to believe for the impossible.

00:20:50.896 --> 00:20:53.951
It's time to achieve the impossible.

00:20:53.951 --> 00:20:55.520
It's time to believe big.

00:20:55.520 --> 00:20:57.749
You've got to start believing God for big.

00:20:57.749 --> 00:21:04.799
Stop thinking so small because God wants to be a big God and operate in your life today.

00:21:16.091 --> 00:21:16.514
You have to understand he is the same yesterday, today, and forever.

00:21:20.760 --> 00:21:20.989
And faith calls those things that be not as though they were.

00:21:20.989 --> 00:21:25.755
And you've got to believe what he said he would do.

00:21:25.755 --> 00:21:28.949
You've got to believe it in your heart.

00:21:28.949 --> 00:21:31.714
You've got to cast out the doubt.

00:21:31.714 --> 00:21:33.909
Say, 'I doubt that doubt, devil.

00:21:37.635 --> 00:21:37.919
I doubt your doubt.

00:21:37.919 --> 00:21:44.137
I refuse to believe what you're telling me, and I refuse to receive what the enemy's report is.

00:21:44.754 --> 00:21:47.051
I'm going to believe what the Word of God says.

00:21:47.051 --> 00:21:55.635
' The doctor might tell you you have a day to live, two days to live, whatever, but I know that nothing is impossible to him who believes.

00:22:10.205 --> 00:22:10.720
I know that he'll heal your body and he'll restore you right where you are if you believe him for it.

00:22:10.720 --> 00:22:14.789
He said he cares for even the sparrows, the lily of the field.

00:22:14.789 --> 00:22:19.051
How much more does he care for you?

00:22:19.051 --> 00:22:20.331
How much more?

00:22:20.331 --> 00:22:21.760
We're joiners of Jesus.

00:22:29.919 --> 00:22:30.101
He loves you.

00:22:30.101 --> 00:22:30.283
Do you understand that?

00:22:30.283 --> 00:22:37.080
Jesus paid the price for you to be free from sickness and disease, from poverty and lack, and from mental torment.

00:22:37.080 --> 00:22:39.930
He paid for it all for you.

